File: The Total Shutdown Movement has vowed to bring Sandton to a standstill. JOHANNESBURG - The Total Shutdown Movement has vowed to bring Sandton to a standstill. Various organisations will march to Sandton to protest against gender-based violence and xenophobia in South Africa. They are set to picket outside the Johannesburg Stock Exchange. READ: Alex Total Shutdown movement threatens Sandton “We want to reiterate that despite the silence of corporate leaders in the midst of this national crisis and their continued business-as-usual attitude in the midst of the scourge of violence against women and girls; we will no longer allow them to continue with the facade of being ‘innocent bystanders’,” the movement said in a statement. South Africa has been gripped by ongoing gender-based violence and attacks on foreign nationals. A number of women have been brutally killed recently.